Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createDensityArea(25.10)                              createDensityArea(25.10)

Name
       createDensityArea - Creates a density screen area

Syntax
        createDensityArea

       [-help]

       <box > <density>[-name <obj_name>]

       Creates a density screen area. A density screen area is a floorplan ob-
       ject used to assign standard cell placement density in the design area.
       The  createDensityArea  command can be used to create partial placement
       blockages even outside the core boundary. Use this  command  after  im-
       porting the design.

       Note:  After  creating the density screen area, you can double-click on
       the object in the design display area to open the Attribute  Editor  to
       change the density value.

Parameters
       <density>
              Specifies the maximum standard cell placement density percentage
              allowed  in  the area. Valid values are in increments of 5: 100,
              95, 90, 85, 80, 75, 70, 65, 60, 55, 50, 45, 40, 35, 30, 25,  20,
              15, 10, 5, 0.

              For  example,  setting  a density percentage of 75 percent means
              that up to 75 percent of the defined density area will  be  used
              for placement.

              Note:  If you enter any number that is not valid, the percentage
              defaults to the nearest valid value.

              Maximum: 100

              Minimum: 0

              Data_type: float, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each createDensityArea parameter. For a detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man createDensityArea

       <box>  Specifies the box in the coordinates of the density area.

              * llx: Specifies the lower left  x  coordinate  of  the  density
                area.

              * lly:  Specifies  the  lower  left  y coordinate of the density
                area.

              * urx: Specifies the upper right x  coordinate  of  the  density
                area

              * ury:  Specifies  the  upper  right y coordinate of the density
                area.

              Data_type: box, required

       -name <obj_name>
              Specifies the name of the density screen area.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command creates a density screen area with placement den-
       sity of 20%:

       createDensityArea 699.6 526.96 1100.22 773.92 20

